value.value: A nuclear medicine image taken of a study participant for use in a clinical trial.
The information and data generated from a final analysis dataset of a clinical trial.
The information and data generated from an interim analysis dataset of clinical trial.
Documentation pertaining to the organization that approves, monitors, and reviews biomedical research to protect the rights, safety and welfare of the study subjects.
The approved guidelines governing the publication of results from a clinical trial.
Records of an event experienced by a subject in a clinical trial, which is defined by the clinical study protocol as significant.
A document intended to capture specific subject-related information through a series of questions.

label.value: Institutional Review Board Independent Ethics Committee Subject Questionnaire

value.value: A document, approved by the Institutional Review Board (IRB)/Independent Ethics Committee (IEC), intended to capture specific subject-related information through a series of questions.
A radiographic image taken of a study participant for use in a clinical trial.
A generally agreed upon set of laboratory values that allow for comparative interpretation of laboratory results, and on which medical decisions are made.

label.value: Clinical Trial Non-Investigational Product Supplies Shipment Documentation

value.value: Records providing information regarding the shipment of supplies being used in a clinical trial that are not related to the investigational product.
Documentation that details the dispensing and return of an investigational product (IP) to and from a subject, and the reconciliation of the IP prior to its return to the sponsor designee.

label.value: Investigational Product and Clinical Trial Supplies Communication Record

value.value: Documentation providing information regarding communications pertaining to the investigational product, and associated trial supplies.
Documentation providing information regarding investigational product (IP) inventory returns to or from a distribution center, depot, and/or trial site.
Documentation detailing the shipment approval, requests, dispatch, tracking, and receipts to and from a distribution center, depot, and/or clinical trial site, of an investigational product (IP).
Documentation detailing the transfer of an investigational product (IP) between depots and clinical trial sites, within or across clinical study protocols.
Documentation detailing the shipment of a laboratory sample.

label.value: Record of Retained Body Fluids or Tissue Sample

value.value: Documentation pertaining to identification and location information of samples being held for possible future (re) testing.
Records pertaining to the statistical data from a clinical trial.
Documentation pertaining to the revelation of a previously masked component of the study.
Records of the results of biochemical analyses, histological examinations, and other tests provided by a laboratory or testing facility.

Records describing relevant findings and notifications of unexpected serious adverse reactions and other safety information, which is submitted by a sponsor to regulatory authorities, investigators, and Institutional Review Boards (IRBs)/Independent Ethics Committees (IECs).

Records containing any interim or final results, as well as clinical and statistical descriptions, presentations, analyses and interpretations of any therapeutic, prophylactic, or diagnostic agent used in human subjects in a clinical trial.

Records pertaining to site initiation-related visits, and a site's completion of requirements to begin participation in a clinical trial, including confirmation that trial procedures have been reviewed by the investigator and trial personnel at the site.
Records describing visits made to a clinical trial site for the evaluation of clinical trial conduct, and regulatory compliance of the site.
Records of relevant data related to a pregnancy and its outcome as experienced by a female subject, or by the partner of a male subject during a clinical trial.
Records informing the regulatory authorities of the progress of a clinical trial.
Records detailing the progress of a clinical trial.

label.value: Final Clinical Trial Close Out Monitoring Report

value.value: Records describing the findings of a site monitor at a site close-out visit prior to a trial's completion.
Records summarizing information and data related to the statistics of the final analysis from a clinical trial.

label.value: Institutional Review Board Independent Ethics Committee Clinical Trial Status Report

value.value: Records sent to an Institutional Review Board (IRB)/Independent Ethics Committee (IEC) of all findings that may adversely affect the safety of a subject, impact the conduct of a clinical trial, alter the IRB/IEC's willingness to continue the trial.

label.value: Institutional Review Board Independent Ethics Committee Report

value.value: Records sent to the Institutional Review Board (IRB) or Independent ethics committee (IEC) at regular intervals, which provides information and updates about a clinical trial.
Records summarizing information and data related to the statistics of an interim analysis from a clinical trial.
Records describing an onsite visit, or other contact experience to determine whether a site is qualified to participate in a clinical trial.
Records describing a serious adverse event that occurred during a clinical trial.

label.value: Institutional Review Board Independent Ethics Committee Subject Diary

value.value: An instrument approved by the Institutional Review Board (IRB)/Independent Ethics Committee (IEC) that is used to record subject data away from a clinical trial site.
An instrument used either to capture a subject's condition or symptoms, or to monitor compliance during a clinical trial or disease treatment while away from the clinical site.
A detailed description of the framework, and process required to build a database for paper and electronic data capture (EDC).
A detailed description that specifies the import, export, and transfer of data.
A detailed description of the requirements by the end user for the use of interactive response technology.
Official records that indicate exclusion from certain rights, privileges and practices.

label.value: Institutional Review Board Independent Ethics Committee Good Clinical Practices Compliance Statement

value.value: A declaration by the Institutional Review Board (IRB)/Independent Ethics Committee (IEC) that it is performing its function according to written operating procedures, and is in compliance with Good Clinical Practices (GCP), or applicable regulatory requirements.

A declaration that proper measures have been taken to ensure that the risk for spreading transmissible spongiform encephalopathy (TSE) through the use of the Investigational Product (IP) has been minimized, which may include being manufactured with materials of a non-animal origin.
A collection of central trial-related communication agreements, significant discussions, or relevant information.
A collection of agendas, presentation materials, and other documents generated for attendees during a central trial-related meeting.
A collection of agendas, presentation materials, and other documents generated for attendees during a centralized test-related meeting.
